{'book': {'publisher': 'Academic Press', 'synopsis': 'The Ontogeny of Vertebrate Behavior is a collection of articles focused on the comparative psychology researches. The text is devoted to the development of vertebrate behavior, emphasizes the ontogenetic determinants, and answers questions related to the differentiation of selected response systems. The book is organized into 10 chapters that feature the concepts of vertebrate behavior and its ontogeny. It presents the study of behavioral development, as well as the visual perceptual systems and its evolution. It explains the perceptual abilities of the human infant and the early experience and problem-solving behavior. Cerebral effects of environmental manipulation and the behavioral phenomena are explained. The book also talks about the ontogeny of emotional, play, and exploratory behaviors; of sexuality and maternal behavior; and of mother-infant relations. It also discusses the principle and procedure of imprinting. Finally, it explains the vocal learning of avian species and the ontogeny of language, as well as the vocal abnormalities. This text will be invaluable to the students, novices, and professionals in psychology, ethology, endocrinology, and behavioral and developmental biology.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/35/02/9780125043502.jpg', 'title_long': 'The Ontogeny of vertebrate behavior', 'edition': 1, 'dimensions': 'Weight: 1.74 Pounds', 'dimensions_structured': {'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 1.74}}, 'pages': 500, 'date_published': '1971', 'subjects': ['Botany', 'Biological Sciences & Nutrition -> Biology -> Botany'], 'authors': ['Howard Moltz'], 'title': 'The Ontogeny of vertebrate behavior', 'isbn13': '9780125043502', 'msrp': 72.99, 'binding': 'Hardcover', 'isbn': '0125043503', 'isbn10': '0125043503', 'other_isbns': [{'isbn': '9780323147507', 'binding': 'eisbncanonical'}]}}